    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel vital though. it feels like i'm just a set of data points. if my slack status stayed 'away' for days, my boss would probably just assume my internet is down or something. no one calls, no one checks in... it’s like i’m already invisible. it almost makes me think that maybe there’s more peace in just letting it happen, you know? just fading out instead of fighting to stay visible.",
